The Presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP and former Vice President, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar has voted at his polling unit of Ajiya in Yola North Local Government Area of Adamawa. The PDP presidential candidate, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, says he looks forward to a successful transition after the election. The Wazirin Adamawa, who voted at his home town in Adamawa, said, when asked to reveal what would be his reaction after the poll that “I look forward to a successful transition. That is what I look forward to.” He expressed satisfaction with the turnout of voters, hoping that the electoral officers would cope with the huge number.  PHOTOS: Massive turnout as Atiku takes campaign to Sokoto PHOTOS: Massive crowd receives Atiku in Akwa Ibom Photos: Atiku launches educational program in Yola